cription': This feature combines systolic blood pressure, heart rate, glucose levels, and total cholesterol, weighted by BMI and adjusted by hypertensive status and whether the patient is on blood pressure medication. It reflects the integrated cardiovascular health and risk.\n'brief description': An integrated score assessing cardiovascular health by merging key health indicators with lifestyle and medical conditions.\n'relevant': ['sysbp', 'heartrate', 'glucose', 'totchol', 'bmi', 'prevalenthyp', 'bpmeds']", "'new_feature': 'cardiovascular_vitality_ratio'\n'detailed description': This feature integrates the normalized glucose and heart rate metrics and combines them with a weighted product of systolic blood pressure (sysbp) and BMI, adjusted by age. It aims to reflect the cardiovascular vitality by considering crucial metabolic and physiological factors.\n'brief description': A composite ratio reflecting cardiovascular vitality by integrating glucose, heart rate, systolic blood pressure, and BMI, adjusted by age.\n'relevant': ['age', 'glucose', 'heartrate', 'sysbp', 'bmi']", "'new_feature': 'cardiovascular_health_ratio'\n'detailed description': This feature is calculated by combining normalized glucose levels and heart rate, with an emphasis on the interaction between smoking habits (currentsmoker and cigsperday) and existing cardiovascular conditions (prevalenthyp and bpmeds). The ratio accounts for patients' lifestyle choices and their impact on cardiovascular health, providing a nuanced understanding of cardiovascular risk factors.\n'brief description': A composite ratio integrating lifestyle and cardiovascular health indicators.\n'relevant': [glucose, heartrate, currentsmoker, cigsperday, prevalenthyp, bpmeds]", "'new_feature': 'cardiovascular_age_adjusted_index'\n'detailed description': This feature combines the impact of age, BMI, glucose levels, and systolic blood pressure in a composite index designed to reflect the cardiovascular health adjusted for the patient's age. It takes into account normalized glucose and BMI to evaluate how age affects cardiovascular health risks, particularly focusing on how well the cardiovascular system can manage stressors associated with aging.\n'brief description': An index combining age, BMI, glucose, and systolic blood pressure to adjust cardiovascular health risks for age.\n'relevant': ['age', 'bmi', 'glucose', 'sysbp']", "'new_feature': 'cardiovascular_health_integrity_index'\n'detailed description': This feature integrates glucose, heart rate, and cholesterol levels to create a composite index reflecting cardiovascular health integrity. The index is further adjusted by age, BMI, smoking status, and diabetes presence to provide a nuanced understanding of an individual's cardiovascular health resilience.\n'brief description': A composite index that reflects cardiovascular health integrity by considering glucose, heart rate, cholesterol, age, BMI, smoking status, and diabetes presence.\n'relevant': [age, bmi, currentsmoker, diabetes, glucose, heartrate, totchol]", "'new_feature': 'age_bmi_combined_index'\n'detailed description': This feature combines age and BMI to assess the cumulative impact of these two factors on health risk, offering a nuanced view of the interplay between body composition and age-related health dynamics. The feature is calculated by multiplying age with BMI and then normalizing the result to ensure it falls within a comparable range for analysis.\n'brief description': A combined index of age and BMI to evaluate health risk factors.\n'relevant': ['age', 'bmi']", "'new_feature': 'cardiovascular_adjustment_score'\n'detailed description': This feature creates an integrated score incorporating the impact of whether the patient is on blood pressure medication (bpmeds), along with their systolic blood pressure (sysbp), glucose level, and body mass index (BMI). It emphasizes the potential adjustment needed for cardiovascular health considering medication influence.\n'brief description': A composite score reflecting cardiovascular adjustment needs, factoring in blood pressure medication, systolic blood pressure, glucose, and BMI.\n'relevant': ['bpmeds', 'sysbp', 'glucose', 'bmi', 'age']", "'new_feature': 'glycemic_stress_index'\n'detailed description': The glycemic stress index is a composite feature that integrates normalized glucose levels with heart rate, adjusted by BMI and age. It aims to quantify the stress placed on the body due to glucose fluctuations and cardiovascular activities, reflecting the metabolic response in relation to body composition and age-related factors.\n'brief description': A composite index combining glucose and heart rate, adjusted by BMI and age, to reflect metabolic stress.\n'relevant': ['glucose', 'heartrate', 'bmi', 'age']", "'new_feature': 'cardiovascular_adaptability_score'\n'detailed description': A composite score reflecting the adaptability of the cardiovascular system by integrating glucose levels, heart rate, and systolic blood pressure, further adjusted by BMI and age, and considering the patient's smoking status.\n'brief description': A score measuring how well the cardiovascular system adapts, considering glucose, heart rate, blood pressure, BMI, age, and smoking status.\n'relevant': ['glucose', 'heartrate', 'sysbp', 'bmi', 'age', 'currentsmoker']"]
