quilibrium.  \n'relevant': ['sysbp', 'diabp']  ", "'new_feature': 'cholesterol_bmi_glucose_ratio'  \n'detailed description': A ratio that leverages cholesterol, BMI, and glucose levels to assess the metabolic and cardiovascular risk in individuals, providing insight into their overall health balance.  \n'brief description': A composite ratio of cholesterol, BMI, and glucose levels to evaluate metabolic health risk.  \n'relevant': ['totchol', 'bmi', 'glucose']", "'new_feature': 'cardiovascular_adaptation_index'  \n'detailed description': This feature evaluates the adaptive capacity of an individual's cardiovascular system, integrating factors such as heart rate variability under stress, systolic and diastolic blood pressure differentials, and BMI adjustments to assess how well the cardiovascular system can adapt to changes in physical and environmental conditions.  \n'brief description': An index assessing cardiovascular adaptability using heart rate and blood pressure metrics.  \n'relevant': ['heartrate', 'sysbp', 'diabp', 'bmi']  ", "'new_feature': 'comprehensive_blood_pressure_index'  \n'detailed description': A combined metric that evaluates blood pressure health by considering both systolic and diastolic pressure, adjusted with consideration for BMI and heart rate to provide a holistic view of cardiovascular stress.  \n'brief description': A holistic measure of blood pressure health factoring in BMI and heart rate.  \n'relevant': ['sysbp', 'diabp', 'bmi', 'heartrate']", "'new_feature': 'vascular_stress_indicator'  \n'detailed description': A composite feature designed to assess the impact of stress on vascular health, combining systolic and diastolic blood pressure with heart rate, particularly focusing on individuals predisposed to hypertension and diabetes.  \n'brief description': An indicator of stress influence on vascular health.  \n'relevant': [sysbp, diabp, heartrate, prevalenthyp, diabetes]  ", "'new_feature': 'cardiovascular_adaptability_index'  \n'detailed description': This feature represents the body's adaptability to cardiovascular challenges, incorporating systolic and diastolic blood pressure, heart rate, and BMI. It reflects how well the cardiovascular system can maintain stability and respond to stress, potentially influencing coronary heart disease risk.  \n'brief description': An index assessing cardiovascular adaptability using blood pressure, heart rate, and BMI.  \n'relevant': ['sysbp', 'diabp', 'heartrate', 'bmi']", "'new_feature': 'hypertension_adjusted_glucose_index'  \n'detailed description': This feature is derived by adjusting the glucose level based on blood pressure metrics and the hypertensive condition of the patient. It aims to assess the impact of hypertension on glucose metabolism, providing insights into the risk of diabetes complications.  \n'brief description': A glucose-based index adjusted for hypertension, linking metabolic and vascular health.  \n'relevant': [sysbp, diabp, glucose, prevalenthyp]  ", "'new_feature': 'vascular_resilience_factor'  \n'detailed description': A composite metric integrating systolic and diastolic blood pressures with BMI to assess the resilience of vascular systems against health risks, particularly in those with prevalent hypertension.  \n'brief description': A metric for vascular resilience based on blood pressure and BMI for individuals with hypertension.  \n'relevant': ['sysbp', 'diabp', 'bmi', 'prevalenthyp']", "'new_feature': 'heart_health_efficiency_ratio'  \n'detailed description': This feature calculates the ratio between systolic blood pressure and heart rate, adjusted for BMI, providing insights into the efficiency of the heart's performance relative to the individual's body composition. Higher values might indicate better cardiovascular efficiency.  \n'brief description': Ratio of systolic blood pressure to heart rate, adjusted by BMI.  \n'relevant': ['sysbp', 'heartrate', 'bmi']  "]
